main event: A potential UFO sighting was reported in St. Louis, Missouri, on October 29, 1966.
interesting points: Photographs taken during the sighting were classified as 35 mm slides, with varying exposure times ranging from 3 to 15 minutes,Scott AFB had UFOs on radar during the time of the sighting,The planetarium in St. Louis suggested that the sighted object was the planet Jupiter,One of the slides showed what appeared to be light sources in the sky,The analysis hinted at multiple objects traveling in similar directions, suggesting airport traffic.
sighted object: unidentified flying objects captured in slides
witness description: Mr. Schlitt, who took the photographs
